In short, both discs have strong analog fidelity and preserved dynamics, but Greatest Hits, Vol. 1 aligns more precisely with my priorities: tape warmth, lyric‑forward yet room‑retaining vocals, tactile midrange and bass, lush harmonies, and restrained transparent mastering rather than the slightly more aggressive, micro‑detailed, punch‑first character of the in‑the‑room mixes.

